SUMMARY:Bachata Tuesdays
DESCRIPTION:Bachata Tuesdays at METROPOLIS VAUXHALL\, 72-73 ALBERT EMBANKMENT\, LONDON\, SE1 7TP \nBachata Tuesdays is London’s longest-running weekly Bachata night\, now in its new home: \nMETROPOLIS VAUXHALL 72 – 73 ALBERT EMBANKMENT\, LONDON\, SE1 7TP \nJoin us every Tuesday for structured Bachata classes in London followed by a huge social party with the best Bachata DJs and dancers from London and beyond. \nWhether you’re a complete beginner or an advanced dancer\, our expert team will help you grow step by step in a fun\, friendly\, and authentic environment. \n🕖 7:00pm – 7:45pm: Footwork & Styling Challenge (Open Level) \nStart the evening with an energetic Bachata footwork and styling class designed to develop your rhythm\, body movement\, and musicality. \nImprove timing & coordination\nBuild confidence through choreography and styling\nSplit focus: Choreography & Musicality OR Styling & Body Movement\nThis class is the perfect warm-up for your body and mind before the partner work classes begin. \n🕢 7:45pm – 8:40pm: Bachata Moderna / Fusion / Sensual (Partner work – 4 Levels) \nDiscover how Bachata is danced outside of the Dominican Republic with a mix of Moderna\, Fusion\, and Sensual styles. \n💃 Choose your level: \nLevel 1: Complete Beginners\nLevel 2: Improvers\nLevel 3: Intermediate\nLevel 4: Advanced\nOur structured Bachata syllabus covers: \nLead & Follow Turn Patterns\nBody Movement\, Waves\, Rolls & Cambres\nFraming & Partner Connection Technique\nMusicality & Rhythm Interpretation\nSafe Social Dancing Practices\nLearn how to blend authentic Bachata technique with modern styling to feel confident at socials and festivals. \n🕣 8:45pm – 9:45pm: Dominican Bachata – Footwork & Partner work \nGo back to the roots with our authentic Dominican Bachata classes in London. Full of flavour\, playfulness\, and joy\, this class connects you to the heart of Bachata’s culture. \nYou’ll learn: \nAuthentic Dominican footwork & partner work\n8 ways to move your hips in Bachata\nSyncopations & rhythmic play variations\nStreet Style vs Dance School Bachata\nHow to interpret instruments (guitar\, bongos\, güira) through movement\nThis class will boost your musicality\, flow\, and cultural connection to the dance. \nWhy Join Bachata Tuesdays at METROPOLIS VAUXHALL? \n🌍 The longest-running weekly Bachata night in London – 14 years strong\n🕺 Classes for all levels: Beginners to Advanced\n📖 Structured syllabus to guarantee progress\n💃 London’s top Bachata teachers & DJs with international reputation\n🎉 Massive weekly Bachata social in VAUXHALL’S new Latin Gem METROPOLIS VAUXHALL.\n⚡ Every Tuesday at METROPOLIS VAUXHALL\, 72 – 73 ALBERT EMBANKMENT\, LONDON\, SE1 7TP . \nLearn\, dance\, and be part of the city’s biggest Bachata community!
URL:https://golatindance.com/event/bachata-tuesdays-at-luxe-london-with-julian-mr-m-and-ritmo-latino-london/2026-03-31/
LOCATION:Metropilis – Vauxhall\, 72 Albert Embankment\, London\, SE1 7TP\, United Kingdom
CATEGORIES:London
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golatindance.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/612169446_1539616580955631_1106507166801717173_n.jpg
END:VEVENT
